-- Hong Kong shares close at highest in 1-1/2 months
-- By Grace Li
-- Wed May 28, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 28 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares closed at their highest level in about 1-1/2 months on Wednesday, tracking gains in other Asian markets as upbeat U.S. economic data lifted sentiment.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed up 0.6 percent at 23,080.03 points, its highest close since April 10. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong jumped 1.1 percent, its highest finish since April 14.  The financial sector was the biggest index boost. Among the top gainers, China Life Insurance <2628.HK> climbed 3 percent and China Construction Bank Corp <0939.HK> added 1.4 percent.